\par\pard\plain \fi360\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 If he had lived another hour longer he would smelled the musky odor of sweat and beak oil wafting down from the top of the ravine. He would have heard the soft patter of footsteps on the dusty road. He would have seen the bark-sheathe boots a man stop right in front of his bush, and he would have felt two blue-grey eyes gawking down at him through the spaces in-between the karkle's twigs. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Two blue-grey eyes, Jandri eyes, belonging to a man named Seb Soreel. They were sparkling, bright and curious, and they narrowed as they searched Mandri\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s bundled body for any sign of life. Seb thought it would be strange to find someone here on the side of the road, but he knew it would be a bad, bad omen if that someone was dead.}
